			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Patent Troll reboot... Sue the end user.
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1771527">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I agree that our current system is strangling industry, but the solution is not to get rid of them entirely.  That would result in startups never ever succeeding because big industry would just adapt any new idea in a fraction of the time it cost the startup to reach market.  It would only favor corporations and the American dream would effectively be dead.<br />
<br />
But there is every reason to scale back the system to what it was originally intended, a short term monopoly.  And I'd consider it reasonable to enforce reasonable royalties.  Especially in the tech sector, you should not be able to hold another company hostage and prevent them from competing entirely.<br />
<br />
There was a recent paper published by the feds about copyright too which was immediately rescinded and denied it ever existed. It was even published by republicans.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
